{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17491426","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17491426"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:46:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:46:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"935"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"935","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/935"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.14,0.08,0.63,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"935"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68016"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"935","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/935"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"935"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53481"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"251"},{"type":"tags","id":"578"},{"type":"tags","id":"1258"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"},{"type":"tags","id":"3817"},{"type":"tags","id":"4046"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5489"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6095"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68016","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/68016"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 72-year-old woman presents with a six-week history of a painless swelling in her left side of neck. She migrated from the Sudan three years ago. She has a forty-pack year smoking history and over the last few months has felt generally tired. She has developed anorexia and early satiety and lost 10 kg of weight. She has a chronic smoker\u0027s cough, but has not noticed any changes in this nor in her sputum. On examination there is a non-tender 2 cm smooth swelling deep to the skin in the left supraclavicular fossa. Examination of her chest and abdomen does not provide any helpful information other than signs of weight loss.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Non-Hodgkin\u0027s lymphoma","Carcinoma of the bronchus","Tuberculosis","Carcinoma of the stomach","Trypanosomiasis brucei"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical picture of anorexia and early satiety, would fit for a diagnosis of carcinoma of the stomach with a metastatic Virchow\u0027s node in her neck. Virchow\u0027s node takes supply from the lymphatic vessels from the abdominal cavity hence it is the sentinel lymph node of the cancers such as the gastric cancer. When the node is visible in the neck, it is known as Troisier\u0027s sign (Image). All the other diagnoses are possible but less likely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENon-Hodgkin\u0027s lymphoma\u003C/strong\u003E patients with metastatic disease will often present with B-symptoms (fever, sweats, weight loss), \u0026gt;1 lymph node involvement and extra-lymphatic involvements.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECarcinoma of the bronchus\u003C/strong\u003E must certainly be considered and excluded in such a long-term heavy smoker but the symptoms appear more GI in origin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETuberculosis\u003C/strong\u003E should be considered in any migrant from a developing nation - but if she had active TB when she left the Sudan, she would likely have presented earlier. The patient may well come from a part of the world where sleeping sickness (\u003Cstrong\u003ETrypanosomiasis brucei\u003C/strong\u003E) is endemic, but it does not usually present in this way. Anorexia, weight loss and somnolence are important clinical features of this disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Anorexia, weight loss and somnolence are common features of cancer-related pathologies."],"references":["Layke JC, Lopez PP. Gastric cancer: diagnosis and treatment options. American family physician. 2004 Mar 1;69(5):1133-40. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/15023013/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53481"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"935"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"16155"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"16155","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/16155"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/a5eae889-82f4-4ba5-8bac-dc99eaab2613.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/a5eae889-82f4-4ba5-8bac-dc99eaab2613.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":292,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53481","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53481"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-08T14:06:18+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-08T14:06:19+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"935"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68016"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/31"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf97","name":"Oncology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"202